subSubSection.paragraph:
Differential diagnosis.
Differentiated from other species by the combination of the very densely coarsely punctate dorsum, the deep pronotal foveae, the subserial or random elytral punctation, and the broadly rounded elytral apices (
Fig. 51
). The metaventral plaques are narrow, almost twice the width separating them (ratios 2/1/7/ 4). The aedeagus (
Fig. 53
) does not suggest placement in any of the groups.
